  "text": "In Apache Kafka, audit logging for authorization decisions is centralized in the StandardAuthorizer implementation. The primary file producing audit log entries for ALLOWED/DENIED authorization events is StandardAuthorizerData.java (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/), which contains the core audit logging logic.\n\nKey components:\n\n1. **StandardAuthorizerData.java** - Contains the authoritative audit logging implementation:\n   - Defines auditLog using 'kafka.authorizer.logger' (line 82, 115-116)\n   - Method logAuditMessage() (lines 281-310) logs authorization decisions:\n     * For ALLOWED results: logs at debug level when action.logIfAllowed() is true (line 292-296)\n     * For DENIED results: logs at info level when action.logIfDenied() is true (line 304-305)\n   - Method buildAuditMessage() constructs detailed audit messages containing principal, operation, resource, host, and authorization decision (lines 254-271)\n   - Method authorize() (lines 228-252) invokes the logging for each authorization decision\n\n2. **StandardAuthorizer.java** - Implements ClusterMetadataAuthorizer interface:\n   - Calls StandardAuthorizerData.authorize() which triggers audit logging\n   - Records authorization metrics via AuthorizerMetrics inner class\n   - Methods authorize() (lines 145-156) delegates to data.authorize()\n\n3. **Action.java** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/) - Defines the audit control parameters:\n   - logIfAllowed() flag (lines 70-72): indicates if ALLOWED access should be logged\n   - logIfDenied() flag (lines 82-84): indicates if DENIED access should be logged\n\n4. **AuthHelper.scala** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/) - Broker-side authorization helper:\n   - Calls Authorizer.authorize() and uses Action with logIfAllowed/logIfDenied flags\n   - Used by KafkaApis and ControllerApis to perform authorization checks\n\n5. **AuthorizationResult.java** - Defines ALLOWED and DENIED enum values for authorization decisions\n\n6. **Authorizer.java** - Interface defining the authorization API used by brokers\n\n7. **KafkaApis.scala** and **ControllerApis.scala** - Use AuthHelper to authorize requests and set logIfAllowed/logIfDenied flags for audit trail tracking\n\nThe audit logging chain flows: KafkaApis/ControllerApis -> AuthHelper.authorize() -> Authorizer.authorize() -> StandardAuthorizer.authorize() -> StandardAuthorizerData.authorize() -> StandardAuthorizerData.logAuditMessage(), which produces the actual audit log entries to the 'kafka.authorizer.logger' logger."
}

